# Compute Engine module

This Terraform module creates a **Google Compute Engine** VM with a boot disk, optional extra persistent disks, VPC networking, optional external IP, service account attachment, startup script, and Shielded VM defaults.

## Features

- **VM instance** — Machine type, zone, deletion protection, optional IP forwarding
- **Boot disk** — Image, size, type, optional CMEK, labels
- **Extra disks** — Map of additional `pd-*` disks attached to the instance
- **Networking** — Subnetwork attachment; optional ephemeral public IPv4
- **Service account** — Optional dedicated SA with configurable OAuth scopes
- **Scheduling** — Standard or preemptible (Spot-style) with safe defaults
- **Shielded VM** — Optional secure boot, vTPM, and integrity monitoring
- **Tags and labels** — Network tags for firewall rules; `environment` and `managed_by` labels merged with yours

## Usage

### Call from another repository

Point `source` at this repo and the path `//Gcp/ComputeEngine`. Pin **`ref` to a tag or commit** in production.

```hcl
module "compute_vm" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/saurabhrsahu/terraform-modules.git//Gcp/ComputeEngine?ref=main"
  # ...same inputs as below
}
```

The **root** module must configure the **Google** provider and credentials. This module only declares `hashicorp/google`.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    google = {
      source  = "hashicorp/google"
      version = ">= 6.47.0, < 8.0.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "google" {
  project = var.project_id
  region  = var.region
}
```

### Basic usage (internal IP only)

```hcl
module "app_vm" {
  source = "../../modules/Gcp/ComputeEngine"

  project_id     = "my-project"
  zone           = "us-central1-a"
  instance_name  = "app-01"
  machine_type   = "e2-medium"
  subnetwork     = "projects/my-project/regions/us-central1/subnetworks/private-apps"

  network_tags = ["app-servers"]

  labels = {
    app = "api"
  }
}
```

### External IP and extra disks

```hcl
module "bastion" {
  source = "../../modules/Gcp/ComputeEngine"

  project_id           = "my-project"
  zone                 = "us-central1-a"
  instance_name        = "bastion-01"
  machine_type         = "e2-small"
  subnetwork           = "projects/my-project/regions/us-central1/subnetworks/public-edge"
  enable_external_ip   = true

  additional_disks = {
    data = {
      size_gb = 100
      type    = "pd-balanced"
    }
  }

  metadata_startup_script = <<-EOT
    #!/bin/bash
    apt-get update -y
  EOT
}
```

## Inputs

| Name | Description | Type | Default | Required |
|------|-------------|------|---------|:--------:|
| `project_id` | GCP project ID | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `zone` | Zone (e.g. `us-central1-a`) | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `instance_name` | Instance name | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `machine_type` | Machine type | `string` | `"e2-medium"` | no |
| `boot_disk_image` | Boot image / family | `string` | `"debian-cloud/debian-12"` | no |
| `boot_disk_size_gb` | Boot disk size (GB) | `number` | `20` | no |
| `boot_disk_type` | Boot disk type | `string` | `"pd-balanced"` | no |
| `boot_disk_kms_key_self_link` | CMEK key for boot disk | `string` | `null` | no |
| `subnetwork` | Subnetwork self link or name | `string` | n/a | yes |
| `network_ip` | Static internal IP in subnet | `string` | `null` | no |
| `enable_external_ip` | Ephemeral external IPv4 | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `network_tags` | Firewall network tags | `list(string)` | `[]` | no |
| `service_account_email` | VM service account email | `string` | `null` | no |
| `service_account_scopes` | OAuth scopes (if SA block set) | `list(string)` | see variables file | no |
| `metadata` | Instance metadata map | `map(string)` | `{}` | no |
| `metadata_startup_script` | Startup script body | `string` | `null` | no |
| `additional_disks` | Map of extra disks `{ key => { size_gb, type } }` | `map(object)` | `{}` | no |
| `preemptible` | Preemptible / Spot-style VM | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `automatic_restart` | Auto-restart (non-preemptible) | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `on_host_maintenance` | `MIGRATE` or `TERMINATE` | `string` | `"MIGRATE"` | no |
| `deletion_protection` | Deletion protection | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `can_ip_forward` | Enable IP forwarding | `bool` | `false` | no |
| `enable_shielded_vm` | Shielded VM settings | `bool` | `true` | no |
| `environment` | `dev`, `stage`, or `prod` | `string` | `"dev"` | no |
| `labels` | Extra labels | `map(string)` | `{}` | no |

## Outputs

| Name | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `instance_id` | API instance id |
| `instance_self_link` | Resource self link |
| `instance_name` | Instance name |
| `zone` | Zone |
| `machine_type` | Machine type |
| `internal_ip` | Primary internal IP |
| `external_ip` | Public IP if enabled |
| `additional_disk_self_links` | Map of extra disk self links |
| `summary` | Short summary object |
| `connection_info` | gcloud SSH / serial hints |

## Requirements

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| terraform | >= 1.3.0 |
| google | >= 6.47.0, < 8.0.0 |

## Providers

| Name | Version |
|------|---------|
| google | >= 6.47.0, < 8.0.0 |

## Notes

- Use firewall rules and IAM (OS Login, IAP) appropriate for your org; this module does not create firewall rules.
- If `preemptible` is `true`, the module sets `automatic_restart = false` and `on_host_maintenance = TERMINATE` as required by Compute Engine.
- Do not set both `metadata["startup-script"]` and `metadata_startup_script` to different values.
